Configure port 1588 timestamp capture once.

Set/Get CPRI port 1588 timestamp capture configuration. This function sets up timestamp capture once when the hfn and bfn in the data path matches with capture_bfn_num and capture_hfn_num. When mode is bcmCpri1588CaptureModeMatchHfnOnly time stamp is captured when hfn matches capture_hfn_num. In RSVD4 hfn becomes lower 8 bits of message group count and bfn becomes upper 12 bits of message group count.

Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portPort number.
[in]directionBCM_CPRI_DIR_TX or BCM_CPRI_DIR_RX
[out]config(IN/OUT) Configuration information.
typedef struct bcm_cpri_1588_capture_config_s {
bcm_cpri_1588_capture_mode_t mode; // Timestamp Capture type
uint32 capture_bfn_num; // if RSVD4, upper 12 bits of message group count
uint32 capture_hfn_num; // if RSVD4, lower 8 bits of message group count
} bcm_cpri_1588_capture_config_t;
// CPRI port 1588 timestamp capture modes
BCM_CPRI_1588_MATCH_BFN_AND_HFN
BCM_CPRI_1588_MATCH_HFN_ONLY

Agnostic configuration set API
Direction Description
Rx direction This API only configures the framer portion. Encapsulation needs to be configured using the agnostic default Queue number 0. Configures following
  • rx framer.
  • Container parser.
  • Encapsulation pipeline.
  • Presentation time control.
  • User needs to configure following using separate API.
Tx direction This API only configures the framer portion. Decapsulation needs to be configured using the agnostic default Queue number 0. Configures following
  • Tx framer assembler.
  • Container parser.
  • Decapsulation pipeline.
  • Presentation time control.

Set and Program Compression Table.

Prorgram the compression lookup table. The look up table is used for compression of the data in either ingress or egress direction. The table entry is 23 bits entry and encoded to represent 16 data look up. Since there is only one compression/decompression engine per AxC, either Compression or decompression can be turn on in only one direction per AxC.

◆ bcm_cpri_port_encap_get()

int bcm_cpri_port_encap_get ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  queue_num,
bcm_cpri_encap_info_t *  encap_config 
)

Configure/Retrieve the encapsulation header info for a given AxC ID.

Configure/Retrieve the encapsulation header info for a given Queue Number (axc_id). This API is used for both CPRI and RSVD4 ports This is the encapsulation of AxC frames into RoE packets which is injected into the Switch ingress Pipeline. Setting up encapsulation for roe packet for given queue.

CPRI Encap configuration
Variable Description
flow_id Flow Identifier. 0xFF is NIL FlowID. In RSVD3 mode 0 - 0xFFF.
subtype Subtype in roe packet
hdr_type : Header type - bcmCpriHdrEncapTypeRoe : 1904.3 RoE encapsulation,
  • bcmCpriHdrEncapTypeNone : No Encapsulation (Used mostly Fast-Eth mode, where the ETH header already exists.,
roe_ordering_info_index Provides the INDEX into the Ordering INFO Table. Each Queue has up to 16 different Ordering INFO compilation options.
macda_index Indicates the 4-bit Destination Addr Look UP.
macsa_index Indicates the 4-bit Source Addr Look UP.
vlan_type - bcmCpriVlanTypeNone: enables ENCAP untagged packets to be created by Encap engine.
  • bcmCpriVlanTypeSingle: enabled ENCAP tagged packets to be generated by Encap engine (Use VLAN_ID_0).
  • bcmCpriVlanTypeQinQ: enabled ENCAP QinQ packets to be generated by Encap engine.
  • bcmCpriVlanTypeSingleTable1: enabled ENCAP tagged packets to be generated by Encap engine, but use the second VLAN_ID_1 ID instead of VLAN_ID_0.
vlan0_idx Choose from the pre-programmed 64 12-bit VLAN_ID_0 lookup.
vlan1_idx Choose from the pre-programmed 64 12-bit VLAN_ID_1 lookup.
vlan0_priority 4-bit VLAN Priority (PCP and DEI) for VLAN0 to complete VLAN info
vlan1_priority 4-bit VLAN Priority (PCP and DEI) for VLAN1 to complete VLAN info
vlan_ethertype_idx Index between the two pre-configured ETHER_TYPE values.
opcode - bcmCpriRoEOpcodeOamTlv : Operation, administration and management packet with type, length and value.
  • bcmCpriRoEOpcodeCtrlAxC : Ctrl_AxC data.
  • bcmCpriRoEOpcodeVSD : VSD Vendor specific control packet.
  • bcmCpriRoEOpcodeTiming : Timing packet A packet containing both timeStamp and seqNum.
type - BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_IEEE1914 : IEEE 1914 RoE frame format
  • BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_RSVD3 : RSVD3 Frame Format
  • BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_ECPRI8 : 8 bytes eCPRI header frame format.
  • BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_ECPRI12 : 12 bytes eCPRI header frame format.
version Header Version used in RSVD3 and 1904 mode. User specified.
ecpri_pc_id PC_ID for eCPRI header, only 16 bits are used.
ecpri_msg_id MSG_ID for eCPRI header, only 8 bits are used.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[in]queue_numQueue Number same as AxC Id.
[out]encap_config(IN/OUT) encapsulation header configuration.
CPRI Encapsulation flags
Encapsulation Flag Description
BCM_CPRI_ENCAP_USE_TAG_ID_FOR_VLAN Use TAG that is generated by the RX framer to index the lookup of FLOW ID. Typically used for CONTROL AxC and single message processing in RSVD4.
BCM_CPRI_ENCAP_USE_TAG_ID_FOR_FLOWID Use TAG that is generated by the RX framer to index the lookup of VLAN ID. Typically used for CONTROL AxC and single message processing in RSVD4.
BCM_CPRI_ENCAP_USE_OPCODE Use opcode in roe packet.
// CPRI VLAN Types
typedef enum bcm_cpri_vlan_type_e {
bcmCpriVlanTypeNone = 0, // No VLAN
bcmCpriVlanTypeSingle = 1, // Single VLAN
bcmCpriVlanTypeQinQ = 2, // QinQ
bcmCpriVlanTypeSingleTable1 = 3 // Single VLAN use Table 1
} bcm_cpri_vlan_type_t;
// CPRI RoE Subtypes refer to IEEE 1914 spec.
typedef enum bcm_cpri_roe_subtype_e {
bcmCpriRoESubtypeControl = 0, // Control
bcmCpriRoESubtypeResv = 1, // Reserve
bcmCpriRoESubtypeAgnostic = 2, // Agnostic
bcmCpriRoESubtypeCpriData = 3, // Structure Aware data
bcmCpriRoESubtypeNative = 4, // Data payload
bcmCpriRoESubtypeSlowCM = 5 // Slow C&M
} bcm_cpri_roe_subtype_t;
// CPRI RoE Opcodes IEEE 1914
typedef enum bcm_cpri_roe_opcode_e {
bcmCpriRoEOpcodeOamTlv = 0, // OAM TLV
bcmCpriRoEOpcodeCtrlAxC = 1, // Control AxC
bcmCpriRoEOpcodeVSD = 2, // VSD
bcmCpriRoEOpcodeTiming = 3 // Timing
} bcm_cpri_roe_opcode_t;
// CPRI Header Encapsulation types
typedef enum bcm_cpri_hdr_encap_type_e {
bcmCpriHdrEncapTypeRoe = 0, // ROE encapsulation type
bcmCpriHdrEncapTypeNone = 1, // no ROE encapsulation
bcmCpriHdrEncapTypeCount = 2 // should be last
} bcm_cpri_hdr_encap_type_t;
// bcm_cpri_roe_frame_format_t - These macros are used to select the frame format selection.
BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_IEEE1914 // RoE in IEEE 1914 frame format
BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_RSVD3 // RoE in RSVD3 frame format
BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_ECPRI8 // RoE in ECPRI8 frame format
BCM_CPRI_ROE_FRAME_FORMAT_ECPRI12 // RoE in ECPRI12 frame format

bcm_gport_t  port,

)

Set/Get the VLAN EtherType configuration for encapsulation header.

This API programs the fields in roe packet header. It programs roe EtherType. There are two choice of EtherType (the EtherType will be selected between them based on VLAN lookup table entry ether_type_index(set using bcm_cpri_port_encap_set). The API also programs vlan information going to roe packet. encap_vlan_tagged : Indicates the ETHER-TYPE value for tagged Ethernet packets generated by ENCAP engine, the lower 16 bits is used in QinQ mode only. For single VLAN case, the upper two bytes are used during encapsulation and lower two bytes are populated based on the QUEUE_VLAN lookup table.

  • 0: Default inner vlan and outer will be 0x8100_0000.
  • 1: Outer vlan and inner will be 0x8100_0000 encap_vlan_qinq: Indicates the ETHER-TYPE value for QinQ Ethernet packets generated by ENCAP engine. The Lower 16bits are place-holder bits, the user programmed values are ignored. In QinQ modes, the lower 16bits come from Queue VLAN lookup table.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[out]vlan_config(IN/OUT) vlan configuration information.
// CPRI Encapsulation VLAN configuration
} bcm_cpri_encap_vlan_config_t;

uint32 ethertype_vlan_tagged; // single tag
uint32 ethertype_vlan_qinq; // QinQ
uint32 roe_ethertype_0; // ROE EthType 0
uint32 roe_ethertype_1; // ROE EthType 1
} bcm_cpri_encap_vlan_config_t;

Setup FEC related timestamp configuration.

Set and get timestamp configuration when fec is enable. When FEC is enabled this API is used to configure FEC related timestamp details. enable : Enables timestamp in FEC case. fec_fifo_ts_source_select : timestamp going to FIFO captured from 66b word or 257b word fec_fifo_ts_source_select : timestamp going to CMIC captured from 66b word or 257b word control_bit_offset_0 : Bit offset when control word in the first code-word in 257b->66b conversion default 0 control_bit_offset_1 : Bit offset when control word in the second code-word in 257b->66b conversion default 0x45 control_bit_offset_2 : Bit offset when control word in the third code-word in 257b->66b conversion default 0x85 control_bit_offset_3 : Bit offset when control word in the first code-word in 257b->66b conversion default 0xC5 This function sets up configuration related FEC, Timestamp functionality need to be turned on using timestamp related api.

◆ bcm_cpri_port_rsvd4_rx_flow_add()

int bcm_cpri_port_rsvd4_rx_flow_add ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  flow_id,
bcm_rsvd4_rx_flow_info_t *  flow_info 
)

Add RSVD4 Rx Flow data AxC.

Add RSVD4 Rx Flow data AxC This API configures flows in rx side. When rsvd4 message header matches with match_data. That message payload is added in given flow.

RSVD4 RX Flow add configuration
Variable Description
flowid Flow identifier.
mask Mask to compare rsvd4 message header.
match_data rsvd4 header data to compare to get the payload in this flow.
payload_size Size of roe packet payload
last_payload_index roe packets in flow have same size but we can have one packet with different payload size at repeated frequency. last_payload_index defines the frequency of different size packet. If last_payload_index is 5, packets 0-3, 5-8 ... will have size = payload_size and packets 4, 9 ... will have last_payload_size.
last_payload_size see last_payload_index
msg_ts_mode Timestamping mode
  • 0 - bcmRsvd4MsgTsModeWCDMA
  • 1 - bcmRsvd4MsgTsModeLTE
  • 2 - bcmRsvd4MsgTsModeGSMDL
  • 3 - bcmRsvd4MsgTsModeGSMUL
sync_mode - bcmRsvd4SyncModeNoSync // Start extraction as soon as matching RSVD4 message is received.
  • bcmRsvd4SyncModeRadioFrame // Start extraction as soon as timestamp field of the message header indicates start of Time Slot. Only valid for msg_ts_mode 2 and 3 bcmRsvd4SyncModeMasterFrame // Start extraction only after the rfrm_offset is equal or smaller than the current message offset in the Master Frame
  • bcmRsvd4SyncModeTsNoSync // Start extraction only after the rfrm_offset is equal or smaller than the current message offset in the Master Frame, and start on beginning of a Time Slot as specified by the timestamp field of the message header. Only valid for msg_ts_mode 2 and 3
  • bcmRsvd4SyncModeTsRadioFrame //Start extraction only after bfn_offset matches the current BFN, and the rfrm_offset is equal or greater than the current message offset in the Master Frame.
  • bcmRsvd4SyncModeTsMasterFrame // Start extraction only after bfn_offset matches the current BFN, and the rfrm_offset is equal or smaller than the current message offset in the Master Frame, and start on beginning of a Time Slot as specified by the timestamp field of the message header. Only valid for msg_ts_mode 2 and 3.
stuffing_count Stuffing count is bit to remove in gsm mode, non gsm mode it is 0.
message_number_offset 12 bit Master Frame counter offset.
master_frame_offset Message offset within Master Frame for synchronization.
msg_ts_count Only valid for msg_ts_mode 2 and 3. Number of messages per time slot. container_blk_count : Number of bits received in master frame (or Number of bits received in time slot in GSM)
priority 0-3 IQ data stream will get the lowest priority. Single Message Control stream will get the highest priority
gsm_pad_size GSM Tail padding removal size
gsm_extra_pad_size GSM Tail extra padding removal size
gsm_pad_en GSM ingress padding removal enable
gsm_ctrl_loc GSM Control TSN location:
  • 1: bits[127:120]
  • 0: bits[63:56] of the last transfer from the RX framer
axc_id The data will be stored in different queue. AxC_id is identifier for the queue. Value can be 0 to 63
queue_size In bytes. In coming data is stored in queue. The queue size is size of buffer for given queue. The queue size is decided based on the bandwidth of given flow.
tsn_bitmap GSM timestamp bit map. 1: Remove extra bytes. 0: No extra bytes removal.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[in]flow_idEquivalent to AxC Id, 0-63 for data
[in]flow_infocontainer parser entry information
// RSVD4 TS MSG modes
bcm_rsvd4_msg_ts_mode_t options are:
BCM_RSVD4_MSG_TSMODE_WCDMA // Msg Timestamp WCDMA mode
BCM_RSVD4_MSG_TSMODE_LTE // Msg Timestamp LTE mode
BCM_RSVD4_MSG_TSMODE_GSM_DL // Msg Timestamp GSM DL mode
BCM_RSVD4_MSG_TSMODE_GSM_UL // Msg Timestamp GSM UL mode
// RSVD4 Sync modes
bcm_rsvd4_sync_mode_t options are:
BCM_RSVD4_SYNC_MODE_NO_SYNC // Sync On Message Offset
BCM_RSVD4_SYNC_MODE_MSG_AND_MASTER_FRAME_OFFSET // Sync On Master Frame and Msg Offset
BCM_RSVD4_SYNC_MODE_TS_NO_SYNC // Sync On Msg Offset timestamp, GSM Only
BCM_RSVD4_SYNC_MODE_TS_MSG_AND_MASTER_FRAME_OFFSET // Sync On Master Frame And Msg Offset timestamp, GSM Only
// RSVD4 Rx Flow configuration
typedef struct bcm_rsvd4_rx_flow_info_s {
uint32 mask; // Mask for message header
uint32 match_data; // header data to match
uint16 payload_size; // roe packet payload size
uint16 last_payload_index; // index of roe packets with different payload size
bcm_rsvd4_msg_ts_mode_t msg_ts_mode;// time stamping mode
bcm_rsvd4_sync_mode_t sync_mode;
uint16 stuffing_count; // bit to remove in gsm mode, 0 in non-gsm mode
uint32 message_number_offset; // 12 bit Master Frame counter offset
uint16 master_frame_offset; // Message offset within Master Frame for synchronization
uint16 msg_ts_count; // Number of messages per time slot, valid for msg_ts_mode 2 and 3 only
uint16 container_blk_count; // Number of bits received in master frame
uint8 priority; // priority of the stream
uint32 queue_size; // queue size of buffers in bytes
uint8 gsm_pad_size; // GSM Tail padding removal size
uint8 gsm_extra_pad_size; // GSM Tail extra padding removal size
uint8 gsm_pad_en; // GSM ingress padding removal enable
uint8 gsm_ctrl_loc; // GSM Control TSN location
uint32 axc_id; // AxC Id can be 0 - 63
uint32 last_payload_size; // last Payload size
uint8 gsm_tsn_bitmap; // GSM TSN bitmap
} bcm_rsvd4_rx_flow_info_t;

bcm_gport_t  port,
int  axc_id,
bcm_cpri_axc_frame_info_t *  axc_info 
)

Set/Get up the AxC(method 1) or AxC group(method 3) on a CPRI port in the Rx datapath.

This API adds AxC (method 1) or AxC Group (method 3). This API configures AxC on a CPRI port.

  • Adds entry to Basic Frame Parser Block. For method#3, the entries need to be equally divided into Na entries.
  • Configures Container Parser Block
  • Configures IQ Packing Buffer (multiple AxCs if method#3).
  • Configures encapsulation pipeline.
  • User needs to explicitly activate the newly added entry. by calling the API bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() staring 6.5.14, bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() API is deprecated and do not need this step anymore. Once this API is call, this new AxC will be active right away. Method#1 Na, Nv and Nc fields are not required and will be ignored. Method#3 All fields are required except stuffing_count.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[in]axc_idAxC Id or base AxC Id for group 0-63.
[in]axc_info(IN/OUT) AxC configuration axc_frame_info
Return values
BCM_E_NONEBCM_E_XXX

◆ bcm_cpri_port_rx_axc_frame_delete()

int bcm_cpri_port_rx_axc_frame_delete ( int  unit,
bcm_gport_t  port,
int  axc_id 
)

Remove the specified AxC (method 1) or AxC group (method 3) on a CPRI port.

This API deletes framer configuration associated with a given AxC ID in RX data path.

  • Removes entry/entries from Basic Frame Parser Block.
  • Clears Entry in Container Parser Block associated with this AxC
  • Clears IQ Packing Buffer ( multiple AxCs if method#3).
  • Clears entry in encap pipeline.
  • User needs to explicitly activate the newly removed entry/entries by calling the API bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() staring 6.5.14, bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() API is deprecated and do not need this step anymore. Once this API is call, this AxC will be deleted right away.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[in]axc_idAxC Id or base AxC id.
Return values
BCM_E_NONEBCM_E_XXX

Set/Get rsvd5 configuration on a port.

Set/Get rsvd5 configuration on a port. Configuration information is populated in the following structure

typedef struct bcm_cpri_rx_rsvd5_config_info_s {
uint32 schan_start; // The first sub-channel allocated for the RSVD5 parser. Valid values are 16 to 63
uint32 schan_size; // Number of sub channels 1, 2 or 4 for CPRI 4x, 8x and 16x.2 or 4 for CPRI 2x and 10x.Setting the field to 0 disables the engine. Values other than 1, 2, 4 not supported.
int disable_parity_check; // True/False
uint32 queue_num; // user configurable
uint32 priority; // 0-3

bcm_gport_t  port,
int  axc_id,
bcm_cpri_axc_frame_info_t *  axc_info 
)

Sets up the AxC (method 1) or AxC group (method 3) in the Tx datapath on a CPRI port.

This API configures framer portion of AxC to a port Applies to both Method#1 and Method #3. This can add single AxC or AxC group.

  • Add entry to Basic Frame Assembly Block
  • Configure Container Assembly Block
  • Configure IQ Unpacking buffer ( multiple AxCs if method#3).
  • Configure de-encapsulation data manipulation.
  • User needs to explicitly activate the newly added entry/entries by calling the API bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() staring 6.5.14, bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() API is deprecated and do not need this step anymore. Once this API is call, this new AxC will be active right away. Notes: Method #1 Na, Nv and Nc fields are not required and will be ignored. Method #3 All fields are required except stuffing_count.
Parameters
[in]unitUnit number.
[in]portSwitch port number.
[in]axc_idaxc_id or base axc_id
[in]axc_infoAxC configuration axc_frame_info
Return values
BCM_E_NONEBCM_E_XXX

Remove the specified AxC (method 1) or AxC group (method 3) on a CPRI port.

This API deletes framer portion of AxC configuration from a port

  • Clear IQ Packing Buffer (multiple AxCs if method#3).
  • User needs to explicitly activate the deleted added entry/entries by calling the API bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() staring 6.5.14, bcm_cpri_port_stage_activate() API is deprecated and do not need this step anymore. Once this API is call, this new AxC will be active right away.
